Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @red onion{1}(finely diced). Pat @shrimp{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

Set aside @?onion{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings).

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add shrimp, @blackening spice{1%tbsp}, remaining onion, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Swap in shrimp for chicken; cook, stirring, until opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

While shrimp cooks, finely dice @Roma tomato{1}(finely diced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, juice from one lime wedge (two lime wedges for 4), and 1 TBSP reserved onion (3 TBSP for 4 servings); add more onion to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, juice from one lime wedge (two lime wedges for 4 servings), and lime zest to taste. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Evenly sprinkle @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} onto one half of each tortilla. Top cheese with filling, then fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Heat a drizzle of oil and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for filling over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add quesadillas and cook until golden brown on the first side, ~{1-2%minutes}. Flip and cook ~{1%minute} more.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

Transfer quesadillas to a #cutting board{}; slice into thirds and divide between plates. Serve with salsa, lime crema, and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Making a fine quesadilla is easy—all you needed was a tortilla, whatever cheese you happened to have on hand, and a microwave. This recipe adds finesse with butter for a golden crust and spiced shrimp.

> You can swap in chicken for shrimp if preferred—cook, stirring, until no longer pink and cooked through.